<b>Subject:</b> A Wizards Poin of View.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2092" TARGET=_self>My opinion.</A> (Darknyss)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Maybe your right about the Pk thing but I am still getting my

<BR>butt kicked constantly at lvl 8. I have never succesfully gated on
<BR>a Cent. when he's pounding me.....but maybe thats because mana is
<BR>short by the time you realize your losing. After 3 shocks of Fire
<BR>you dont have the mana to cast it anyway. My AC suck big time.
<BR>I cant hit with a dagger for more than 8 points. oh...thats when we
<BR>do hit. Root is a good spell, except when the Slaver surprises you
<BR>and stuns you so you cant attack. Roots casting time lends it more for traping a dying orc or before combat when you can kill from a safe distance(which gives no xp). Fire bolt is a nice spell, mine usually does 45 Damage,but ittakes too long to cast in close combat and uses a bunch of mana. No Wiz's arent the Uberclass.I think any Lvl8 warrior would clean my clock.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
